transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Hi, I'm calling to cancel my prescription, please.

Speaker 1: Okay, what's your name and date of birth?

Speaker 2: Okay, first name Eugene, E-U-G-E-N-E.

Speaker 1: Last name Emily Mary, O-R-D as in David, A.

Speaker 2: Date of birth is May 16, 1970.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay, and you say you want to repeat that again? How can I assist you?

Speaker 1: I'd like to cancel my prescription and not receive your product anymore, please.

Speaker 2: Okay, and what's going on? Is it that you have no supply at this time?

Speaker 1: I'm not using it, thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay, so if you're not using it at this time, then I can always go ahead and just pause your prescription, Eugene.

Speaker 1: And you can always give us a call to reorder if you need any supply.

Speaker 2: Okay, that's fine. I won't get any automatically then, correct?

Speaker 1: It will be paused for right now, yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay, you're all set. Have a nice day.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.
